Details
Why
We
Picked
It
Founded
in
2009,
Payoff
is
an
online
lending
platform
that
connects
prospective
borrowers
with
fixed-rate
credit
card
debt
consolidation
loans
in
every
state
except
Massachusetts,
Mississippi,
Nebraska
and
Nevada.
Though
Payoff
only
offers
loans
for
credit
card
debt
consolidation,
it’s
a
top
choice
for
borrowers
with
fair
to
good
credit,
with
more
qualified
applicants
able
to
access
the
platform’s
lowest
rates.
Plus,
applicants
can
complete
a
prequalification
process
to
see
what
kind
of
rates
they
qualify
for
without
damaging
their
credit.
Payoff
offers
pretty
flexible
lending
terms
(two
to
five
years)
and
borrowers
can
borrow
as
little
as
$5,000
or
as
much
as
$40,000,
depending
on
the
credit
card
balances
they
need
to
consolidate.
Rates
are
relatively
competitive
on
the
low
end
(5.99%)
and
the
highest
possible
rate
(24.99%)
is
still
lower
than
some
other
lenders
that
cater
to
borrowers
with
fair
credit.
However,
like
some
lenders,
Payoff
does
not
offer
an
autopay
discount.
And,
while
Payoff
charges
a
0%
to
5%
origination
fee,
there
are
no
late
fees,
annual
fees
or
prepayment
penalties.
Finally,
while
Payoff
does
not
offer
borrowers
a
mobile
app,
the
platform’s
customer
support
team
is
available
seven
days
a
week
so
it’s
easy
to
get
in
touch
when
you
need
to.
Payoff
also
features
a
support
center
and
FAQs
page—both
of
which
offer
a
ton
of
helpful
resources
for
prospective
and
current
borrowers.
Extra
Details
Eligibility: 
Prospective
Payoff
borrowers
should
have
a
minimum
credit
score
of
640
to
qualify
for
a
debt
consolidation
loan.
To
be
eligible,
applicants
must
also
have
a
minimum
credit
history
of
three
years,
zero
current
delinquencies,
a
minimum
annual
income
of
$40,000
and
a
debt-to-income
ratio
under
50%.
The
platform
also
will
evaluate
each
applicant’s
credit
utilization
ratio
and
current
lines
of
credit.
Payoff
does
not
offer
borrowers
a
co-signer
option,
so
applicants
must
qualify
based
on
their
individual
financial
circumstances.
Loan
uses:
 
Payoff
only
offers
loans
for
credit
card
debt
consolidation,
making
this
the
most
limited
lending
platform
on
our
list
of
the
best
personal
loans.
Turnaround
time:
 
After
submitting
an
application
and
all
the
necessary
documents,
underwriting
may
take
three
to
seven
business
days.
After
getting
approved
and
signing
the
paperwork,
you
will
receive
the
funds
within
three
to
six
business
days,
according
to
a
representative.
Pros
Competitive
rates
that
already
include
an
origination
fee
Excellent
customer
service
Ability
to
change
payment
date
once
every
12
months
Cons
Only
offers
personal
loans
for
credit
card
consolidation
Charges
an
origination
fee
Limited
repayment
terms
