Why
We
Picked
It
A
sister
company
to
Rocket
Homes
and
Rocket
Mortgage
by
Quicken
Loans,
Rocket
Loans
offers
personal
loans
through
Cross
River
Bank.
The
lender’s
availability
in
most
states
and
low
minimum
credit
score
requirement
make
Rocket
Loans
an
accessible
option.
However,
borrowers
will
face
origination
fees
and
repayment
terms
limited
to
three
or
five
years.
Rocket
Loans
may
be
a
good
option
if
you
have
a
fair
credit
score
(580
or
higher)
and
want
funds
fast.
However,
the
platform
charges
an
origination
fee
between
1%
and
6%
of
the
loan
amount
and
APRs
range
from
7.161%
to
29.99%,
so
cheaper
loan
options
may
be
available,
depending
on
your
creditworthiness.
Overall,
Rocket
Loans
stands
out
because
of
the
low
credit
score
requirement
and
potentially
fast
funding
time.
The
platform
also
makes
it
easy
to
manage
personal
loans
with
the
user
dashboard
and
customer
support
team,
which
is
available
Monday
through
Saturday.
Extra
Details
Eligibility:
 
Prospective
Rocket
Loans
borrowers
must
have
a
minimum
credit
score
of
580
to
qualify
for
a
personal
loan;
however,
the
average
borrower
score
is
710.
Borrowers
also
should
have
a
minimum
credit
history
of
two
years.
That
said,
the
average
credit
history
of
a
Rocket
Loans
borrower
is
much
longer—18
years.
Finally,
Rocket
Loans
requires
borrowers
to
have
a
minimum
annual
income
of
$24,000
and
a
maximum
debt-to-income
ratio
of
40%,
but
borrowers
average
$85,000
and
14%,
respectively.
Rocket
Loans
does
not
allow
co-signers
or
co-applicants.
Loan
uses:
 
Rocket
Loans
borrowers
can
use
personal
loan
funds
for
home
improvements,
auto-related
expenses,
travel
and
vacation
and
other
large
expenses.
Personal
loans
also
may
be
used
to
consolidate
other
debt,
but
Rocket
Loans
will
not
pay
third-party
lenders
directly.
Loan
funds
cannot
be
used
for
education
expenses
or
expenses
related
to
illegal
activities.
Turnaround
time:
 
Approved
borrowers
can
receive
their
loan
funds
on
the
same
day
they
apply,
if
they
complete
their
application
and
sign
the
promissory
note
before
1
p.m.
Eastern
time
on
a
business
day.
This
means
that
same-day
funding
is
possible,
but
the
average
time
to
receive
funds
is
two
to
four
days.
Pros
Prequalification
process
only
requires
a
soft
credit
check
Offers
same-day
approval,
and
same-day
funding
may
be
possible
Does
not
impose
a
prepayment
penalty
Rate
discount
available
with
autopay
Cons
Fees
for
origination,
late
payment
and
insufficient
funds
Does
not
offer
direct
payment
for
debt
consolidation
loans
Doesn’t
allow
co-signers
or
co-applicants
Limited
loan
repayment
terms
Tips
for
Comparing
Personal
Loans
Consider
these
tips
when
comparing
personal
loans:
Where
possible,
prequalify.
Many
personal
loan
providers
offer
prospective
borrowers
the
ability
to
prequalify
for
a
loan.
This
means
the
applicant
can
submit
details
about
their
financing
needs,
income,
housing
situation
and
other
relevant
information
to
find
out
what
kind
of
loan
amounts,
rates
and
repayment
terms
they
are
likely
to
qualify
for.
Even
better,
this
process
typically
only
requires
a
soft
credit
inquiry
so
you
can
shop
around
without
hurting
your
credit
score.
Consider
the
purpose
of
your
loan.
While
personal
loans
can
be
used
for
a
pretty
broad
range
of
purposes,
they
are
limited
to
things
like
consumer
debt
consolidation,
home
improvements,
vacations,
weddings,
funerals,
large
purchases
and
other
personal
expenses.
For
that
reason,
lenders
often
restrict
the
use
of
personal
loans
for
postsecondary
education
expenses,
business
purposes
and
illegal
activities,
at
a
minimum.
When
considering
a
lender,
confirm
that
your
intended
use
of
the
loan
is
permissible
under
its
borrower
agreement.
Keep
an
eye
out
for
additional
fees.
Some
lenders
offer
fee-free
personal
loans
that
don’t
require
borrowers
to
pay
origination
fees
,
late
payment
fees,
prepayment
penalties
or
any
other
common
loan
costs.
However,
this
is
more
the
exception
than
the
rule,
so
it’s
important
to
ask
about
fees
when
shopping
for
the
best
loan
terms.
And,
if
a
lender
charges
an
origination
fee,
find
out
whether
it’s
built
into
the
APR
or
taken
out
of
the
loan
amount
prior
to
funding,
as
this
may
impact
the
loan
amount
you
need
to
request.
Evaluate
the
lender’s
customer
support
options.
If
you’ve
found
a
lender
that’s
prepared
to
offer
the
money
you
need
at
acceptable
terms,
there’s
one
more
thing
to
consider
before
signing
the
loan
agreement.
While
customer
support
may
not
seem
like
a
big
deal
in
the
honeymoon
phase
of
your
loan,
it
can
make
a
huge
difference
if
you
encounter
issues
with
payments
or
face
a
financial
hardship
during
your
repayment
period.
Review
the
lender’s
customer
service
resources
and
read
reviews
from
past
and
current
borrowers
to
make
sure
it’s
a
good
fit.
Methodology
We
reviewed
15
popular
lenders
based
on
16
data
points
in
the
categories
of
loan
details,
loan
costs,
eligibility
and
accessibility,
customer
experience
and
the
application
process.
We
chose
the
10
best
lenders
based
on
the
weighting
assigned
to
each
category:
Loan
details:
20%
Loan
cost:
35%
Eligibility
and
accessibility:
20%
Customer
experience:
15%
Application
process:
10%
Within
each
major
category,
we
also
considered
several
characteristics,
including
available
loan
amounts,
repayment
terms,
APR
ranges
and
applicable
fees.
We
also
looked
at
minimum
credit
score
requirements,
whether
each
lender
accepts
co-signers
or
joint
applications
and
the
geographic
availability
of
the
lender.
Finally,
we
evaluated
each
provider’s
customer
support
tools,
borrower
perks
and
features
that
simplify
the
borrowing
process—like
prequalification
options
and
mobile
apps.
Where
appropriate,
we
awarded
partial
points
depending
on
how
well
a
lender
met
each
criterion.
